cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.SC, cs.MS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of distributed memory and Charm++ for parallel computing. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper focuses on the Fast Multipole Method, which is a numerical method for solving N-body problems. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Verification) is a possibility as the paper discusses the use of a finer control over communication, which could be seen as a form of symbolic computation. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a possibility as the paper discusses the performance of the FMM code and compares it to previous codes. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possibility as the paper discusses the challenge of hiding the overhead of Charm++ and improving the performance of the FMM code.
